Deborah Roberts could have given up long ago.
I just knew that I wanted to do this.”Her parents did not understand her passion.
“My daddy hated art and said it was never going to be nothing,” Ms. Roberts said.
“He would say, ‘What are you doing that for?’”“I learned to get a thick skin when I was about 25,” she added.
“Nothing anyone can tell you is ever going to make you stop doing it.”